725364f-d.title: Queens: 48th Street - 21st Avenue
725364f-d.text:
48th Street, east side, betweenn Twenty-firat Avenue
and Old Bowery Bav Road, showing four views of the J.M.
Cooper house of 1852. It was the Titus residence until
1922. View number four shows the area surrounding the
house prior to its being parceled and sold.

725367f-b.title: Queens: 48th Street - 21st Avenue
725367f-b.text:
48th Street, east side, north of 21st Avenue, showing the
J.M. Cooper House of 1852. Mr. Sperr calls it the Colonel
Eing House, whereas Mr. Armbruster, who took other photographs
of the dwelling, states that it is the Cooper House of 1858 and
lster the Titus residence.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  May 27, 1934
